ield_10704":null,"resolutiondate":"2015-05-08T18:39:39.509-0500","customfield_10705":null,"customfield_10309":null,"workratio":-1,"lastViewed":null,"watches":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/EUCA-9747/watchers","watchCount":5,"isWatching":false},"created":"2014-07-21T16:03:05.142-0500","customfield_12000":null,"priority":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/priority/2","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/priorities/critical.svg","name":"Critical","id":"2"},"customfield_12400":null,"customfield_12201":null,"customfield_10300":null,"customfield_10102":null,"customfield_12600":"{}","labels":["regression"],"customfield_10301":null,"customfield_11700":null,"aggregatetimeoriginalestimate":null,"timeestimate":null,"versions":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/version/14205","id":"14205","description":"Eucalyptus 4.0.1","name":"4.0.1","archived":false,"released":true,"releaseDate":"2014-08-13"}],"customfield_11901":null,"issuelinks":[{"id":"27103","self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issueLink/27103","type":{"id":"10103","name":"Relates","inward":"relates to","outward":"relates to","self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issueLinkType/10103"},"outwardIssue":{"id":"27333","key":"EUCA-8722","self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issue/27333","fields":{"summary":"Instance timeout and instance status checks","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"priority":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/priority/3","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/priorities/major.svg","name":"Major","id":"3"},"issuetype":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/issuetype/1","id":"1","description":"A problem which impairs or prevents the functions of the product.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/secure/viewavatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=14803&avatarType=issuetype","name":"Bug","subtask":false,"avatarId":14803}}}}],"assignee":null,"updated":"2016-06-06T16:32:51.485-0500","status":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/status/6","description":"The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are closed can be reopened.","iconUrl":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/images/icons/statuses/generic.png","name":"Closed","id":"6","statusCategory":{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/statuscategory/3","id":3,"key":"done","colorName":"green","name":"Done"}},"components":[{"self":"https://eucalyptus.atlassian.net/rest/api/2/component/11301","id":"11301","name":"Broker","description":"Broker-style component for interfacing hypervisors"}],"timeoriginalestimate":null,"description":"Found in recent testing that vmware instances which are orphaned are not always restored. I originally found this due to networking conflicts in my churn tests, colliding with the orphaned instance(s)'s addr(s). \r\n\r\nSteps taken in the test to produce this...\r\n\r\n-Reduce the orphan timeout properties to something small (ie.< 5 ): \r\n{code}\r\nPROPERTY\tcloud.addresses.maxkillorphans\t1\r\nPROPERTY\tcloud.addresses.orphangrace\t1\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n-Run an instance in the vmware cluster.\r\n-Take note of the esx host which is running the VM, block in/out ip traffic to the esx host. I blocked traffic from the CLC and CC/Broker using the following example script:\r\n{code}\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\nnode=$1\r\necho \"blocking node $node\"\r\niptables -A OUTPUT -j DROP -d $node -m comment --comment matt_test\r\niptables -A OUTPUT -j DROP -d $node -m comment --comment matt_test\r\n{code}\r\n-Attempt to terminate the instance\r\n-The instance should go to 'shutting down', and eventually the node should go to not ready. \r\n-Wait for the instance to transition to terminated. Issue another terminate or wait for the instance to be deleted from the  system. \r\n-Restore ip connectivity to the esx host, the following script can be used to restore iptables:\r\n{code}\r\n#!/bin/bash\r\nnode=$1\r\necho \"clearing node $node\"\r\niptables -D OUTPUT -j DROP -d $node -m comment --comment matt_test\r\niptables -D OUTPUT -j DROP -d $node -m comment --comment matt_test\r\n{code}\r\n\r\n-Wait for the CC/Broker to query the esx hosts for VMs, monitor the logs, wait, etc.. \r\nI let the system sit for about 24 hours and did not see the instance restored in Eucalyptus. The instance remained powered on. See config with Euca annotations below. \r\n{code}\r\nconfig = \r\n      (VirtualMachineConfigSummary){\r\n         name = \"i-83b21677\"\r\n         template = False\r\n         vmPathName = \"[datastore1] i-83b21677/i-83b21677.vmx\"\r\n         memorySizeMB = 256\r\n         cpuReservation = 0\r\n         memoryReservation = 0\r\n         numCpu = 1\r\n         numEthernetCards = 1\r\n         numVirtualDisks = 2\r\n         uuid = \"564d0756-2e69-df7a-9388-ccb167dca3c2\"\r\n         instanceUuid = \"520644c6-28da-5e38-ff59-7931c45969c5\"\r\n         guestId = \"otherLinuxGuest\"\r\n         guestFullName = \"Other Linux (32-bit)\"\r\n         annotation = \"Eucalyptus instance i-83b21677\r\ncreated 2014-07-19T15:18:43\r\nby user AIDH6A0MSAZ1FXWOA7FNR\r\non esx node 10.111.5.69\r\nby broker 9178c997\r\nrunning on node a-18.qa1.eucalyptus-systems.com\r\npart of cloud 2720204e\"\r\n      }\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\n-M\r\n","customfield_13000":null,"customfield_13200":null,"customfield_11300":null,"customfield_11500":null,"timetracking":{},"customfield_10005":null,"customfield_10401":null,"customfield_10600":null,"customfield_12900":null,"attachment":[],"aggregate